-- ⚠️ RE-PINNED 2026-07-14 — THE S2 INVERSION (ACCEPT/"IMPL" -> located REJECT).
-- This is NOT the Fork-2 carve-out.  Fork 2 keeps dispatch when the RECEIVER is the
-- ENCLOSING function`s dict-bound `=>` constraint var (see
-- accept_constrained_receiver_shadow, which still prints 14).  Here the receiver is a
-- concrete `Box 3` and the `Num a =>` sits on the SHADOW`s own signature — so this is
-- just the d2 cell (definer shadow, live-impl receiver) with a constrained standalone.
-- Under standalone-wins the standalone takes the call, and `Box` has no `Num` impl:
-- a located `No impl of Num for Box` — clause S9`s specified reject direction.
-- Everything below describes the OLD rule and is kept for the history only.
--
-- S-1 CONTROL (must never regress): the same constrained shadow, but the receiver's
-- head HAS an impl of the shadowed interface, so the occurrence must DISPATCH to the
-- impl, not fall back to the standalone.  This arm worked before the S-1 fix and is
-- exactly what a "just reorder the guard chain so the dict arm wins" repair would
-- have broken (EDictAt carries no route and cannot dispatch).  Must print IMPL.
data Box = Box Int

interface Sz a where
  size : a -> String

impl Sz Box where
  size _ = "IMPL"

size : Num a => a -> a
size x = x + 1

main = println (size (Box 3))
